node.text: When chains drag on the road, they leave sparks. And sparks can cause a wildfire - especially if you're in a drought like the West. Please be careful, cross those chains!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: 🐻👉🚫🔥🌲 It's #WorldEmojiDay, how's your emoji game? Tell me how #OnlyYou will prevent wildfires, emojis only! 👇

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ONLY 75t SMOKEY YOU! EST. 1944'.

node.text: I love when artists imagine me in their style! Thank you @gabo.ghoul for this retro rendition! Have you made any Smokey Bear art? Tag me, I'd love to see!

node.text: As my pal alroker says, wildfires can happen anywhere - even in your neck of the woods! When there are parched and windy conditions, you've got to be extra careful with fire. #OnlyYou can prevent unwanted, human-caused wildfires

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 08, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: These dedicated wildfire prevention adventurers are taking their Smokey Bear trailer on a trip across America! Maybe you'll see them out on the road 👀 (📷: @SmokeyBearFans)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SMOKEY FIREWORKS CAN CAUSE WILDFIRES DON'T LET YOUR FUN TURN INTO FLAMES! FLAMES'.

node.text: Happy #IndependenceDay! Let's show our country some love by leaving the fireworks to the pros. #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 03, 2021. May be an image of standing and text that says 'Itsagrand old forest, too! SMOK Be careful.'.

node.text: Wildfire season doesn't take a break for the 4th of July - please be careful tomorrow! #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires by checking local burn bans and skipping DIY fireworks displays. Refresh your wildfire prevention skills at SmokeyBear.com

node.text: What national parks and forests are on your summer vacation list? Let's protect our public lands this summer by being fire-smart! Wildfire season is here, and #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires. ( 📷: @calslayton)

node.text: It's #TakeYourDogtoWorkDay, but this past year has felt more like take your work to dog day! Shoutout to Remi for helping me spread the word about wildfire prevention. ( 📷: @remisroadtrip)

node.text: Due to climate change, wildfire seasons are more intense than they used to be - forests may take generations to recover. Please do your part to protect them. #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on June 21, 2021.

node.text: Wildfire prevention never goes out of style 😎 ( 📷: @ldb859)
